Differential Diagnosis.
Overall body shape robust and small (
Table 3
). Colour of the few specimens at hand is uniform except most have faded due to dry preservation. The sulcus on the fastigium of the vertex is minute and short. Antennal scape very broad and with a dorsal flange (
Fig. 10B
); pedicel not especially modified; flagellum not annulate (
Fig. 10A
). Male cercus distinctive (
Fig.10N
); tenth tergite with elongate projection, modified apically (
Figs 10I, N
); subgenital plate (
Fig. 10H
) narrowing apically, styles elongate; titillator (
Fig. 10M
) without any sclerotised parts. Female (n=1) with tenth tergite unmodified; cercus rather prominent, stout; subgenital plate triangular, elongate, apex acute, without median carina. Ovipositor elongate, very feebly upcurved, unarmed.

Head.
Head not strongly slanting; frons smooth, shining (
Fig. 10A
); fastigium of vertex very short, with minute sulcus (
Fig. 10B
); eye very large for size of head (
Fig. 10C
); median ocellus small, positioned at base of triangular frontal fastigium (
Fig. 10C
), lateral ocelli absent.

Thorax.
Pronotum with surface smooth, shining (
Figs 10D
); lateral lobe shallow (
Fig. 10A
) not concealing thoracic auditory structure; anterior margin of disk straight to feebly concave (
Fig. 10D
), posterior margin truncate. Thoracic auditory structure small, ovoid, not hidden be pronotum. Prothorax with elongate spines, meso- and metathorax each with tubercles.

Tegmina.
Tegmina delicate, surface clothed with sparse, dark brown setae and feebly sclerotised (
Figs 10F, G
) venation reduced but with two prominent elongate veins; stridulatory file (
Fig. 20E
) very short, appearing swollen; mirror poorly defined and without any internal venation.

Abdomen.
Tenth tergite (
Figs 10I, N
) with extraordinary lateral extensions, apically modified. Cercus simple but fairly large, without internal armature. Phallic complex without any sclerotised portions (
Fig. 10M
).

Female.
Differs from male in following characters. Size slightly larger (
Table 3
); tegmina apparently absent or wholly concealed beneath pronotum. Tenth tergite unmodified; cercus straight but stout. Ovipositor very elongate (
Table 3
), gracefully, feebly upcurved, without armature.
